    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate leaning heavily on **Kyle Tucker** (74.43) and **Drake Baldwin** (70.94) as our primary anchors. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a high-upside matchup against May, where wind-aided conditions (+5%) and a favorable platoon profile push his projection into elite territory. Meanwhile, **Drake Baldwin** is our most efficient catcher play today; despite a decent arm in Freeland, the combination of his #2 spot in the order and a park factor that heavily favors his approach makes him a high-floor start. **Sam Antonacci** also earns a recommendation (64.32) thanks to his leadoff duties and a favorable matchup against Canning, with his high xwOBA metrics suggesting he is due for a productive outing.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (51.19), who remained on the outside looking in. While his talent profile is elite, the optimizer prioritized the positional flexibility and situational platoon edges of **Josh Jung** and **Jackson Merrill**\u2014the latter of whom is thriving today against a high-xERA opponent in Kay (5.66). We are monitoring the risk profile of **Coby Mayo** (53.39), who faces a formidable arm in Fried; while wind blowing out provides a slight buffer, he remains a marginal start. We continue to monitor the status of **Luis Robert Jr.**, who remains sidelined on the IL, as his absence continues to put a ceiling on our stolen base potential for the 5x5 categories. As always, keep an eye on official lineups for **Jacob Wilson** and **Heliot Ramos**, whose projection volatility is tied closely to their finalized spots in the batting order.",
